Ian gets dressed up to join in a battle re-enactment, before trying his hand at product quality testing at one of the surviving weaving mills. Rugby is another huge source of pride in Hawick and Ian makes his debut at the famous Mansfield Park

programme.title: Saturday Kitchen Best Bites: 01/02/2026
programme.desc: Matt Tebbutt presents recipes from Nathan Outlaw, Rupy Aujla, Daisy Terry and Paul A Young, while comedian and actress Jo Brand tucks into either her food heaven or hell

programme.title: Mary Berry - Love to Cook: For a Crowd
programme.desc: The culinary expert meets those who get pleasure out of cooking for a crowd. In Liverpool, she joins the team from Homebaked Bakery, a goal kick away from Liverpool FC's stadium, who take on the job of feeding fans on match day. She also meets Andrew, whose passion to feed has led him to build a smokehouse in his suburban garden. Between these tales, Mary cooks up her own crowd-pleasing delights, including a platter of sticky soy and ginger pork, and a lamb rogan curry

programme.title: Best Bakes Ever: Episode 4 (Shortened)
programme.desc: In light of Britain's baking obsession, actress and cake expert Jane Asher presents a selection of recipes from television chefs, including James Martin, Mary Berry, Paul Hollywood, the Hairy Bikers, Raymond Blanc, Nigella Lawson, Tom Kerridge, Lorraine Pascale and Rachel Khoo

programme.title: Monty Don's Rhineland Gardens
programme.desc: Monty travels to the Netherlands, where the Rhine divides into a network of waterways that eventually flow into the North Sea. Criss-crossing these channels, he discovers how the Rhine has shaped Dutch life, the land and the culture for centuries - as well as visiting the biggest display of tulips in the world and the busiest flower market

programme.title: Clive Myrie's African Adventure: Durban
programme.desc: The second leg of Clive's adventure takes him to Durban, known for its surfing beaches and chilled atmosphere, it's also the biggest city in the KwaZulu-Natal province, ancestral home of the Zulu people. He joins an anti-poaching team saving South Africa's critically endangered rhinos from extinction. He also visits a surf school teaching homeless and disadvantaged kids to surf - and to transform their lives

programme.title: Flog It!: Derby 3
programme.desc: Paul Martin is joined by experts Michael Baggott and Caroline Hawley on a visit to Haddon Hall in Derbyshire, where the team picks out a selection of interesting antiques and collectibles to be sold at a local auction. Michael finds an impressive scent bottle, and Caroline gets a glimpse into the past by looking through a stereoscopic viewer. Paul also looks around the property, and meets the current owner, Lord Edward Manners

programme.title: A Bridge Too Far
programme.desc: Fact-based drama recreating the famous Second World War battle for Arnhem, as Allied forces try to capture a series of strategically important bridges and cut off the Germans from their retreat through Europe. Starring Robert Redford, Anthony Hopkins, Michael Caine, Sean Connery, Dirk Bogarde, James Caan, Edward Fox and Laurence Olivier. Based on the book by Cornelius Ryan, and directed by Richard Attenborough

programme.title: Ski Sunday: 01/02/2026
programme.desc: Ed Leigh and Chemmy Alcott present all the news, gossip and action from the piste, including the latest World Cup events. Plus, reports on British competitors and a look ahead to the Winter Olympics in Italy

programme.title: Eddie the Eagle
programme.desc: Biopic of British sporting underdog Eddie Edwards. Determined to fulfil his dreams of becoming an Olympic athlete, Edwards trains as a ski jumper - a field in which Britain had no other competitors. He secures a place in the 1988 Winter Olympics, where his can-do attitude makes him a media sensation in the face of a losing streak. Starring Taron Egerton, Hugh Jackman and Christopher Walken

programme.title: Top Gear: Top Gear Winter Olympics Special
programme.sub-title: Top Gear Winter Olympics Special Season 7, Episode 7
programme.desc: Jeremy Clarkson, Richard Hammond and James May head to Norway to find out how a selection of cars fare when taking part in Winter Olympic events. Their experiments include firing a rocket-powered Mini off a ski jump, tackling the biathlon with 4x4s, staging a game of motorised ice hockey and timing the Jaguar XK in a speed-skating race

programme.title: Confessions of a Killer: Judgement Day
programme.desc: Conclusion of the two-part documentary about the 1991 murders of Lesley Howell and Trevor Buchanan. Colin Howell details his staged suicide pact as police probe Hazel Stewart's complicity, coercion claims and the disturbing secrets that push the case toward its decisive appeal ruling

programme.title: Saltburn
programme.desc: Working class Liverpudlian student Oliver Quick is a socially awkward square peg in the polished round hole of Oxford University. A random act of kindness lavished on dashing aristocrat Felix Catton grants Oliver access to a summer of decadence at his new friend's palatial family estate, and a dangerous cycle of lust and envy. Comedy thriller starring Barry Keoghan and Jacob Elordi

programme.title: Cyrano
programme.desc: Poet and swordsman Cyrano de Bergerac can improvise a poem while fighting a duel, but is too self-conscious to woo the love of his life. Seeking an outlet for his feelings, he helps a handsome but shy friend to win her heart through love letters. Musical romance, starring Peter Dinklage, Haley Bennett and Kelvin Harrison Jr

programme.title: Question Time: 29/01/2026
programme.desc: Fiona Bruce presents the topical debate, inviting a panel of politicians and other guests King's Lynn, Norfolk, to answer questions from an invited audience on subjects that have made the headlines over the past week

programme.title: Waterloo Road
programme.desc: Darius takes charge in Stella's absence, only for the return of a familiar face to stir old tensions. Cat tries to support Portia but ends up making things worse and Donte turns to his peers as he struggles to handle a disruptive Forest. New mum Coral returns from maternity leave and immediately locks horns with Steph Haydock, while a shocking revelation forces Stella to see everything in a new light

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two

programme.title: Bargain Hunt: Detling 5
programme.desc: Two teams of friends compete in Detling, Kent, assisted by Jonathan Pratt and Catherine Southon. Eric Knowles monitors the contest and also meets art historian Howard Smith to discuss how Rupert Bear started out in a newspaper comic strip in the 1920s, before becoming the character in yellow tartan trousers so beloved today

programme.title: The Repair Shop
programme.desc: The popular series returns after an 11-week break. Three sisters from Shropshire being in a treasured relic from their family's salon - a retro sit-down hairdryer that once belonged to their beloved mum. The rest of the items are a fragile silk rugby flag dating from a 1936 international match between Ireland and England, a delicate collection of hand-carved Nigerian figurines and a battered cornet case that has seen four generations of active service

programme.title: Match of the Day: 01/02/2026
programme.desc: Highlights of the latest Premier League matches, including Tottenham Hotspur v Manchester City at Tottenham Hotspur Stadium and Manchester United v Fulham at Old Trafford. Spurs had won three of their last four meetings with the Citizens, including a 2-0 win at Etihad Stadium in this season's reverse fixture. United and Fulham drew 1-1 when the sides met at Craven Cottage in August, with Emile Smith Rowe rescuing a point for the Londoners. Plus, Aston Villa v Brentford and Nottingham Forest v Crystal Palace

programme.title: BBC News: 02/02/2026
programme.desc: The latest national and international stories as they break

programme.title: Politics Live: 02/02/2026
programme.desc: The latest stories from Westminster and beyond

programme.title: Bridge of Lies
programme.desc: Ross Kemp presents the quiz show where a team of four take on the Bridge of Lies. One by one, they must cross the bridge, stepping on the truths and avoiding the lies. Here, family members Shellie, Scott, Lara and Piers take on the challenge

programme.title: Unbeatable
programme.desc: Jason Manford hosts the general knowledge quiz in which four contestants compete over three rounds to find a single 'unbeatable' answer and streak ahead of the rest to make the final where they can win a cash prize

programme.title: The Boss
programme.desc: Quiz hosted by Susan Calman in which one contestant becomes the Boss and has to use judgement and tactics to decide which player is best suited to answer questions

programme.title: The Vintage French Farmhouse
programme.desc: Three dealers head to the French town of Pezenas in search of antiques, picking up items including a French bamboo-effect mirror and a pair of 1930s mustard yellow chairs

programme.title: Who Do You Think You Are? USA: America Ferrera
programme.desc: Actress America Ferrera searches for a connection to a father she barely knew, and discovers in Gregorio Ferrera a great-grandfather who led multiple revolts against the Honduran government and left an enduring mark on that nation's history

programme.title: Scotland from the Sky
programme.desc: James Crawford begins his journey with a lost canal just outside Glasgow, and then travels back to the heyday of airship travel, the abandoned island of Mingulay. He also discovers the dark history of Inchkeith Island in the Firth of Forth, and ends on the Isle of Lewis, where archaeologists have recently discovered what might be a lost stone circle

programme.title: Flog It!: Sheffield 14
programme.desc: Antiques experts James Lewis and Anita Manning peruse items brought in by members of the public at Sheffield's Cutlers' Hall. Among the treasures on display include a rare set of lead toys and an unusual selection of ceramic dogs. Meanwhile, presenter Paul Martin meets the only person in the country still making surgical steel instruments by hand

programme.title: Richard Osman's House of Games: Week 15: Tuesday
programme.desc: Fatiha El-Ghorri, Patrick Grant, Mr Motivator and Lauren Oakley test their general knowledge skills in a variety of trivia-based games across the week

programme.title: Clive Myrie's African Adventure: Lagos
programme.desc: Nigeria is known as the giant of Africa and in this leg Clive heads to Lagos, one of the continent's largest cities. In a bustling downtown market, he gets a workout with a team who are getting the market-goers fit, and he meets an organic chef in an open-air seafood market to pick up some fresh red snapper, shrimp and prawns. He also hits the studio with talented young musicians and experiences the vibrancy of Nigerian art

programme.title: Global Eye: 02/02/2026
programme.desc: A look at the foreigners lured to fight on the frontline for Russia, while Lyse Doucet reports from Damascus on the challenges of building a new Syria more than a year on from the fall of Bashar al-Assad

programme.title: Celebrity Mastermind
programme.desc: Clive Myrie presides over the first heat as Maryam Moshiri, Chesney Hawkes, Desiree Burch and Danny Robinstake to the famous black chair, answering questions on the Bridget Jones films, the Beatles' White Album, actress Viola Davis and the Star Wars TV series, The Mandalorian. The second round sees them tackling general knowledge questions in a bid to carry off the commemorative trophy

programme.title: Only Connect: Strigiformes v Thrifters
programme.desc: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts as 2023 winners the Strigiformes take on the Thrifters, who took the series 19 title the following year. The teams try to make connections between things that at first do not appear to be linked, with one set of clues comprising skin lutrinae, adipose strigiformes, diluted birds, and flatulent drying cloths

programme.title: University Challenge: Imperial v Warwick
programme.desc: Amol Rajan asks the questions as Imperial College London takes on the University of Warwick in the quarter-finals, with the teams looking to pick up the first of the two wins they need to reach the semi-finals

programme.title: Lover, Liar, Predator
programme.desc: Documentary following four women who discovered they had each been coercively controlled by the same man, and joined forces to end their nightmare and bring him to justice. Jenni, Natalie, Shannon and Robyn waive their anonymity to tell their story in chilling detail, laying bare the confusion, intricacies and frightening realities of coercive control, and revealing how they became trapped by serial predator and sex abuser Aaron Swan. The film unpicks how he got away with his crimes for so long, despite twice being placed on the sex offender register

programme.title: Newsnight: 02/02/2026
programme.desc: Insights and global interviews on the news stories of the day, presented by Victoria Derbyshire

programme.title: Weather: 02/02/2026
programme.desc: The latest forecast

programme.title: What We Do in the Shadows: Laszlo's Father
programme.desc: Laszlo's father's ghost returns to make amends, while Nadja and Nandor deal with the shapeshifters who have moved in next door. Guest starring Steve Coogan

programme.title: What We Do in the Shadows: March Madness
programme.desc: Laszlo and Nandor try to exorcise the demon who has possessed their neighbour Sean. Comedy, starring Matt Berry and Kayvan Novak

programme.title: Retreat
programme.desc: A couple go to stay on an isolated island to sort out their marital difficulties, where they find a mysterious stranger washed up on the beach. He tells them that a virus has wiped out most of Europe, but they are unsure about whether to believe his story, or if he has a sinister reason for deceiving them. Thriller, with Jamie Bell, Cillian Murphy and Thandiwe Newton
